d ($\\lambda~\\gtrsim$ 50\n$\\mu$m) is not as high as suggested by some recent work. We further show that\nthe need for two infrared AGN continuum templates could be related to nuclear\nobscuration, where one of our templates appears dominated by the emission of\nthe extended polar dust.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Feb 2021 19:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-12"}
